<br>
There are a million things to do in this game, and the reason that so many of us are addicted to it is because it appeals to a wide range of tastes.  I've seen father and son playing together, husband and wife, brother and sister, college buddies, and met people from all over the world...  some people will only group with guildmates or their real life friends, and others will only play with people they don't know.  <br>
<br>
The point is, there are a million things that people do in this game in the pursuit of their own version of fun that doesn't sound like fun at all to me.  But that is a good thing, not a bad thing.  If everyone thought it was fun to do the same thing - we'd all have to wait in huge lines!<br>
<br>
If they stink in a group because they solo'd too much or were powerleveled or whatever, leave the group and don't group with that person again.  I've met people like that before too... and I'm sure that at times (God forbid) people have felt that way about me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
<br>
And just to be at odds with the speed theory on soloing... I know a cleric who went from 0-50 in 13 playing days and did probably 90% or more of it in groups.<br>
