<br>
The group is of ideal makeup. Me, a Warrior, a Cleric, an Enchanter, a Shaman, and a Wizard.<br>
<br>
The Warrior does not pull unless specifically told to. Each time. The Wizard does not realize that his insanely uber 1000+ damage AE nukes break the Enchanter's mez, causing all of the 6 mobs that our super warrior pulled to attack and kill the Wizard, the Enchanter, and the Cleric, in that order, in about the same amount of time. The Enchanter insists that a Shaman's speed buffs are better than an Enchanter's. He should know, as his other account was a level 25 Shaman which he swapped with some &quot;other stuff&quot; for this level 54 Enchanter. The Shaman is convinced that his stat and melee buffs make him a tank. Meanwhile, my exp bar is hauling ass. To the left.<br>
